\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  pentadactylis} : Cushions small, rather lax; leaves dark green, hard and rigid; petiole c. 1 mm wide, longer than the lamina; leaf-segments 1-1·5 mm wide, linear-oblong, divaricate. Petals c. 4·5 mm, usually contiguous, white. 2n = 16+5B.{\i  Siliceous rocks. Pyrenees, and rarely in the mountains further south.}
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  willkommiana }(Boiss. ex Engler) Rivas Martínez, {\i Anal. Inst. Bot. Cavanilles}{\b  21}: 229 (1963): Cushions larger, fairly compact; leaves medium green, fairly soft; petiole c. 1·5 mm wide, about equalling, or shorter than, the lamina; leaf-segments 1·5-2 mm wide, oblong, divaricate. Petals c. 5 mm, white. 2n = 32.{\i  Siliceous rocks. Mountains of N. & C. Spain, from the Cordillera Cantabrica and the Cordillera Iberica to the Sierra de Gredos}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp.{\b  losae} (Sennen) D.A. Webb,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  95}: 249 (1987) ({\i S. losae} Sennen, {\i S. pentadactylis} subsp. {\i losana} (Sennen) Malagarriga): Cushions small, very compact, with more or less columnar leafy shoots. Leaves hard and rigid; petiole about equalling the lamina and sometimes nearly as wide, much wider than any of its segments, which are short and forwardly directed. Petals probably c. 4 mm, white.{\i  Limestone rocks, mostly at c. }1000{\i  m. Mountains of N.E. Spain, from Alava prov. to Teruel prov}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b almanzorii} Vargas,{\i  Anal. Jard. Bot. Madrid}{\b  43}: 457 (1987): Petiole much longer than the lamina, and much wider than its segments, which are 0·5-1 mm wide, short and slightly divaricate. Petals 3·5 × 1·5 mm, not contiguous, greenish-yellow. {\i Siliceous rocks. Sierra de Gredos}.
\par

