\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 96. S. fragilis} Schrank,{\i  Pl. Rar. Horti Monac.}, t. 92 (1822) ({\i S. corbariensis} Timb.-Lagr.). Glabrous and with sessile glands, as in {\b 95}, but only slightly viscid. Stems woody at the base, sparingly branched, forming rather lax cushions. Leaves shining, rigid, brittle and rather coriaceous, 12-35 mm wide, divided almost to the base into 3 primary lobes; these are further divided, giving 5-9(-13) narrowly oblong, flat (not sulcate), obtuse to subacute segments. Flowering stem 10-22 cm, with 5-20 flowers. Petals 7-14 × 4-7 mm, white.{\i  Limestone rocks and screes, usually shaded, up to }2000{\i  m, but mostly below }1000{\i  m. • E. Spain and S. France}. Ga Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp.{\b  fragilis} ({\i S. geranioides} subsp. {\i corbariensis} (Timb.Lagr.) Rouy & Camus): Leaves 18-30 mm, wide, usually with 7-11 segments. Flowering stem 10-25 cm. Petals 9-13 mm, oblanceolate; stamens at least 3 mm longer than the sepals. 2n = 60-66. S. France (Corbieres) and N.E. Spain.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp.{\b  valentina} (Willk.) D.A. Webb,{\i  Bot. Mag. }{\b 180}: 186 (1975) ({\i S. valentina} Willk., {\i S. corbariensis} subsp. {\i valentina} (Willk.) D.A. Webb): Leaves 12-25 mm wide, usually with 3-7 segments. Flowering stem 6-15 cm. Petals 7-11 mm, obovate-elliptical; stamens exceeding the sepals by 1 mm or less. 2n = 64. {\i E. Spain, from C. Teruel to E. Jaen.}
\par

